# H.cap.sdd

Scope: Latin uppercase H prototype glyph.

## Must

- Establish uppercase stem weight.
- Establish cap height behavior.
- Provide a straight-sided control glyph for spacing comparisons.
- Keep the crossbar position reviewable as a family-level rhythm decision.

## Must not

- Carry decorative ideas not already permitted by `design-principles.sdd`.
- Solve spacing through kerning.

## Owns

- Uppercase vertical stem logic.
- Cap-height straight-form sidebearings.
- Crossbar weight and placement proposal.

## Depends on

- `../../design-principles.sdd`
- `../../masters/regular.sdd`
- `../../metrics/spacing.sdd`

## Forbids

- Asymmetric sidebearings unless explicitly justified by drawing logic.

## Done when

- H works in `HHH`, `HOH`, `OHO`, `HnH`, and `HaH` proof strings.
- Human review accepts stem weight and crossbar placement as a usable control point.

## Proof-Control Note

- This spec is retained as a legacy proof control for SpecDD system integrity.
- Primary design-DNA for Phase 1 is now `adhesion` (`a d h e s i o n`).
- `H/O/n/o/a` remain as cross-project controls during early validation.